      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "DON'T BREW IT (4) boasts a strong record this course with two wins and two minors from five tries. Recorded a 0.8 lengths win (26.39) in a Grade 5 last time at this track. Has the ability and looks a key chance here. SHOWMAN BAZ (6) was strongly fancied latest and proved too good with a 1.5 lengths win at Wentworth Park in a handy 29.70. Jumping from the pinch draw but has the ability and in winning form. Comes out of a solid form race last start. Can make it back-to-back wins. LIGHTNING LOTTE (8) was strongly supported last start when a short priced favourite and duly saluted winning by 2.25 lengths at this track in a handy 19.34. Outside box to overcome but has a good record over this journey. Leading chance again.",
